:: CH1: Advisor defends King {"position":"1250,1075","size":"100,100"}
The advisor--or rather, Ruyi--sighed. "I was one of the many high-ranking soldiers in his troops back when we were at war with the unrest states." He said as he walked amongst the shops slowly, allowing you to leisurely pick and clamor at the various trinkets. 

Yet your curiosity to hear more of his past rather than roam was keen. Ruyi continues, his eyes now faraway and immersed in memories. "Back then, we knew him as General Di Xin. He was...fierce in battle, and an amazing strategist. He was loyal to us and we were to him, comrades in arms as you may say. All those years have forged him now, with harshness and decisiveness." 

"I understand you must be confused of my loyalty, but I know the man who sits upon that throne, regardless of who's by his side." Ruyi said, though you noticed how his tone turned bitter by the end. 

It was plain to you that Ruyi disliked a certain person person to the King's side, that Daji figure. But his loyalty was true and sound--Ruyi is a soldier, a man of fidelity.

The pair of you walked in silence, the racket of merchants covering your muddled thoughts. You are reminded of [[that black smoke|CH1: First visit Lutai with advisor]] once more, now closer to you than before.


:: CH1: Big decision: Bad outlook {"position":"1200,700","size":"100,100"}
With a bow, a servant presented your bone to the King. As you watched in anticipation, his shoulder tensed and jaw twitched. Yet you are rooted to your spot, fear overflowing your limbs, trembling the body. They say the new Shang King is unlike his predecessors, violent in battle and fierce in conquers. You feel the weight of that truth upon you now, as the King's attention drifts from the bone to you, face clouded in cold fury.

"You would have the cosmos declare the dynasty in peril?" He thundered, smacking the goblet within his hands, the expensive wine spreading across the floor in a loud clatter. You dared not to remind him that [[you are but a spokesperson, not a prophet|History: Who Answered the Diviner]]. You shook from the crisp sound, your breaths coming sharp and swifts. 

"Take them outside." The King said with a scowl. "Grant them fifth whips under the midday sun." The words registered and dread pooled into your belly as you hear rather than see the guards walking to your side. 

"My king, if I may."

[[One of the advisors|First impression of the advisor]] aside the court had risen and spoke. "Diviners are merely conductors of cosmos' pattern, and our newest diviner merely showed the future of Shang may face obstacles. But with you in charge, my King, there is no cause to worry."

As you marvel at the advisor for his unexpected aid, Daji had leaned in and whispered into the King's ear. 

"Yes, yes." The King hummed. "Away with the whips, my favored is not in the mood. And you," he tilted his chin at you, and you hastily bowed. "Away as well."

You exited the court swiftly, ears ringing. Still reeling from the punishment that would have been, you see the advisor who spoke walking away as well. [[Oh, how you must speak to him out of thanks.|CH1: first meeting the advisor]]


:: CH1: Big decision: Good outlook {"position":"1000,700","size":"100,100"}
With a bow, a servant presented your bone to the King. As you watched in anticipation, a thunderous laughter escaped from him, the sound only paused when the King took a long swig of wine from the goblet within his hand. Daji continued to comb his robes, her smile indulging. 

They say the new Shang King is unlike his predecessors, violent in battle and fierce in conquers. It seems that at this hour, you are fortuitous to not bear witness to his warring nature. 

"I knew of it." The King declared, "indeed, your processions are true to the Qiang's esteem in divination." A swell of pride expanded at your chest at the unexpected praise. Such a feat it was, garnering the favor of the King at your first ritual! 

"Leave us now," The King said with a wave of his hand. You bowed, and exited the hall. 

Content at the King's response, you hummed and strolled from the palace. You were about to head towards the market, when a voice behind you spoke. 

"Ah, you must be the diviner my father called forth from Qiang." 

You turned in complete shock and hastily dropped into a bow in front of a young man, whom must be the prince. "Your Highness!" You scrambled for words. "Forgive me, I'm simply surprised to see you about. To what do I owe the pleasure?"

"Well, I witnessed your skill at divination just a few moments ago, and I wished to know you, of course." Said the prince. "I have always been curious of the process. Won't you join me for a walk in the marketplace?"

You were astounded. The prince himself wishes to speak with you as a companion to the city?


[["Of course, your Highness. I thank you for your guidance."|CH1: First meeting the prince: accept]]
[["I'm grateful for your offer, but won't it trouble your time?"|First meeting the prince: decline]]


