:: CH1: First visit Lutai with advisor {"position":"1200,1200","size":"100,100"}
"That smoke? It's from the workers building Lutai, you see." Said Ruyi. "Come, I'll show you."

You followed suit as he walked forth, trekking towards the billowing smoke, and found youself standing at the foot of a grand terrance, levels upon levels, surrounded by few wooden beams of support as workers milled by, carrying heavy stones.

"Our King builds this grand terrance to hold all treasures we've earned with years at war," Ruyi explained, as your eyes wander from the white marble walls to the warm glow of engraved agate. "This place is built for celebration and leisure enjoyments--a true gift for all our suffering for this kingdom."

This must be the reason the King was careless of your lack of treasures, you thought. All that pleasures and fine gifts he seeked may be too much, even for Lutai.


