:: CH1: Prince praises the King {"position":"925,1075","size":"100,100"}
The prince's brow tilted. "Well, in honesty I wondered if I could learn." He said. "Of course, it's impossible for me with my responsibilities as heir, but I suppose I wanted to advise my father, in a way."

Your curiosity grew, and you asked him what he meant. 

The prince smirked. "Father is the best King our kingdom has ever seen, of course." He said, with an air of certainty that compelled you to agree. "He was a war hero before he was king, and he was a fierce general bringing upon glory. He is the proud sun of Shang and our court his pride." 

"Each and every one in court respects him, and I the most. I wish I'd contribute, to live up to his name, you see. But he's yet to let me advise in court." The prince said, though you noticed how his tone turned bitter by the end. 

It was plain to you that the prince disliked a certain person person to the King's side, that Daji figure. But you'd witnessed idolation of his Father. If not prideful, the prince is a man of candor, and his respect rang true.

The pair of you walked forward, the racket of merchants covering your muddled thoughts. You are reminded of [[that black smoke|CH1: First visit Lutai with prince]] once more, now closer to you than before.





:: CH1: Reading the Bone {"position":"1100,550","size":"100,100"}
As you ran your eyes over the bone, you felt yourself frown at how there were far more ominous cracks than auspicious ones.

It is ritual process for a diviner to inscribe beside the cracks indicating good omens and leave the ominous cracks without comment, before the King proceeds with his interpretation.

You knew that if you left the ominous cracks without inscriptions, the King will read this bone as a sign of the state's ill-boding fate instead of a glorious future. You hesitateed, and the King's chilling stare urges you to complete the ritual.


[[You decide to inscribe the good omens as well as the ominous cracks as auspicious. |CH1: Big decision: Good outlook]]
[[You decide to inscribe the good omens but leave out the ominous cracks, as it is meant to be.|CH1: Big decision: Bad outlook]] 


:: CH1: Ritual {"position":"1100,425","size":"100,100"}
//
~ (Date in the form of Shang Dynasty) ~

~ Zhaoge ~
//

You were wrong about the King, it seems. 

Just when you were sure the King's urgency for your arrival is but an exaggeration, you had been called in haste to perform divination. You stand in front of the royal palace, your back against his tall form as your hands hovering under a prepared scapula, holding a torched hardwood brand that's slowly biting a dip in its underside. 

"Tell me," the King had said, his body draped over the carved throne, the infamous Daji to his side, her palm massaging into his shoulders. "Will the Shang thrive on in glory?" And as lazy his tone was as his form, the steel in his eyes chilled you.

You felt his stare even now, unseeing his face. But no matter. To you, the oracle bone's ritual process has been written into your mind, from [[years of practice back in the Qiang state|Context: Qiang 2]]. Your hand moved, almost mindlessly, aligning the scorched hollows from bottom to top as your eyes searched for patterns, cracks, signs. 

The preparations are soon finished in making. [[You leaned forward to take a look at the cracks.|CH1: Reading the Bone]]


